Message.Issue: 'BuilderPlug' contains field 'BuilderPlug.preferencesform' that is of IDisposable type: 'PreferencesForm'. Change the Dispose method on 'BuilderPlug' to call Dispose or Close on this field.
Modify 'BuilderPlug.Dispose()' so that it calls Dispose(true), then calls GC.SuppressFinalize on the current object instance ('this' or 'Me' in Visual Basic), and then returns.
Ensure that 'BuilderPlug.Dispose()' is declared as public and sealed.
Because it is a P/Invoke method, 'BuilderPlug.GetWindowLong(IntPtr, int)' should be defined in a class named NativeMethods, SafeNativeMethods, or UnsafeNativeMethods.
